smart contract cannot stop someone from pocketing it and walking away. (And=
 since the money for the purchase needs to be in dollars in a dumb old bank=
 account, the smart contract probably can=E2=80=99t stop someone from steal=
ing it either.)=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Conceivably the answe=
r is =E2=80=9Cthe DAO is actually a limited liability company under Delawar=
e law, and the LLC agreement and Delaware law constrain the members of the =
LLC to do what the DAO says.=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s not clear to me whether =
